<br>
Pet casts Instill (root spell) infrequently, not enough to count on as per earth pets, but enough that once in a while it might prove useful.<br>
<br>
Really likes the stun spell, and really likes to chain cast when given the chance. Moves in for melee when mob is low hitpoints (granted, I was testing this in S. Ro so vs. tougher mobs I do not yet know what it does).<br>
<br>
The shielding spell is new and does not stack with Burnout.<br>
<br>
NPC wizards (I tested the ones in Neriak) are also casting Instill and Elnerick's Entombment of Ice. They didn't really live long enough for me to see what else they were casting. My pet was getting pushed around a lot more and once poofed into the wall, so be careful if you're at a level where these guys are a challenge still.<br>
<br>
Also, it looked to me like a Necromancer NPC (possibly the one from the next house down the block) was wandering instead of staying in his location. His pet was stuck guarding the wizard house when I got there and he wandered in a few minutes later. I don't know if someone previously pulled him to there or if his pathing has changed or if he's a new mob to add difficulty to this XP camp (or extra experience, depending on how you look at such things <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) I didn't check his con but his pet was green at 56.<br>
