Ahh, but they do.  Or so I conclude from my own test.  I went to Felwithe to do some banking and shopping and set my level 52 Fire pet on the soulbinder (for those who don't know, they never die from damage and never agro)<br>
<br>
At first he was lasting non stop, so I went and did my errands.  10 minutes later I returned to see him simply meleeing and very rarely casting a combust spell. (is that the lowest mana cost spell they cast in battle?)<br>
<br>
I took screenshots where you can clearly see about 10 &quot;taunting attacking, Master&quot; texts between the casts of combust.<br>
<br>
I assume his mana had run out and was blasting his lowest level spell when the mana regened enough for a blast.<br>
<br>
Hmmmm, maybe I should see if he'll take a Clarity 2?  =)<br>
<br>
I'll grab my nearest Chanter friend and drag him to a soulbinder for my next test.<br>
<br>
Another thought is that maybe the newest DD spells they cast take a lot more mana and they can only cast a few of them before being too low to cast more.  And since they'll cast the lowest combust spell as it becomes available during a fight, you'll never see it casting the high ones until it meds between battles?<br>
<br>
If we can somehow get it's mana regen higher it might deal out even more damage on a longish fight.  <br>
<br>
Or perhaps, we should hold off on sending him in on a long battle till the middle so his best spells are available during the key part of the battle?  Maybe back it off after it starts meleeing and let it med before sending it back in to blast some more?<br>
